  "texts": [
    "31), they enjoy a wider and more flexible scope of application given the large number of protein sequences available compared to structures.",
    "They are bettersuited for linear B cell epitopes, but they are potentially useful also for conformational ones by capturing, thanks to the context-aware representations from protein language models (Box 2-3), functional dependencies between amino acids far apart along the sequence but proximal in the 3D structure 31.",
    "ML methods like AlphaFold [65] [66] [67], trRosetta 68, and RoseTTAFold 69 can bridge this scale gap between sequence and structure data availability by enabling predictions of protein structure from sequence alone with unprecedented accuracy.",
    "Predictors of protein structure have huge potential still to be fully explored for the design of immunogens guided by structural insights 59, 70, as well as for antibody and TCR engineering.",
    "Antibody-specific predictors have been proposed [71] [72] [73] [74] based on deep learning architectures similar to AlphaFold, TrRosetta and RoseTTAFold."
  ]
}